<plot>TO YOU SWEETHEART, ALOHA is a one-hour documentary which follows the 94th year in the life of the colorful Honolulu-born 'ukulele master Bill Tapia, exploring not only the charismatic musician and his unique stamp on the creation of Hawai'ian jazz, but also the consummate showman and the endearing storyteller who seeks the fountain of youth.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?610053</url></doc>
